<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. Microscopic features of Hebeloma flavidifolium (E. Horak 13406) A spores x 2000 B basidia x 1000 C cheilocystidia x 1000 D pleurocystidia x 1000 E pileipellis (section of subcutis below epicutis) x 500. Scale bar: 10 µm x 2000, 20 µm x 1000 and 40 µm x 500. Drawing E. Horak." , "Figure 1. ML topology of concatenated ITS and MCM 7 sequences of Hebeloma and Alnicola. Flammula alnicola is used for rooting purposes. Bootstrap support based on 500 replicates and posterior probabilities based on a BI analysis are indicated at the branches. Assignment of species to sections follows Beker et al. (2016). Sequences in red are from Malaysian collections discussed in this paper. T indicates type collections. Thick branches indicate full support. AS - Asia, EU - Europe, NA - North America, O - Oceania, gr. - group." , "Figure 3. Microscopic features of Hebeloma flavidifolium holotype (E 00204812) A spores in Melzer's reagent x 1600 B spore ornamentation in Melzer's reagent x 1600 C cheilocystidia in Melzer's reagent x 500 D cheilocystidia in Melzer's reagent x 1000 E cheilocystidia in KOH x 1000 F pleurocystidia in KOH x 1000. Scale bars: 10 µm (A-F). Photographs H. J. Beker. G Exsiccata (a section of photograph from http: // data. rbge. org. uk / herb / E 00204812 provided by the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh)." , "Figure 4. Microscopic features of Hebeloma flavidifolium (E. Horak 13406) A spores in Melzer's reagent x 1600 B spore ornamentation in Melzer's reagent x 1600 C cheilocystidia in KOH x 500 D cheilocystidia in KOH x 1000 E basidium in KOH x 1000 F pleurocystidia in KOH x 1000 G caulocystidium in KOH x 1000 H ixocutis section (showing thin gelatinous epicutis) in KOH x 125 I epicutis hyphae in KOH x 500 J subcutis below epicutis in KOH x 500. Scale bars: 10 µm, 100 µm (H). Photographs H. J. Beker." , "Figure 2. Macroscopic features A Hebeloma flavidifolium (E. Horak 13406) B H. lactariolens (E. Horak 13381) C H. parvisporum (E. Horak 12796) D H. radicans holotype (E. Horak 13265). Photographs E. Horak." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502270" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502271" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502274" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502272" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502273" .

